bureauXPN.cstext: I WAS LATE ON THIS TRADELINE BECAUSE OF AN ACCIDENT AT WORK. AFTER BEING IN THE HOSPITAL FOR SEVERAL MONTHS, I HAD NO INCOME, THEREFORE I COULDN'T PAY ANY BILLS. ONCE I GOT OUT OF THE HOSPITAL, I COLLECTED ALL MY BILLS AND MADE A LIST OF HOW MUCH I OWED EACH COMPANY. ONCE THAT WAS DONE, I WAITED UNTIL I GOT MY FIRST PAYCHECK, AND DIVIDED THAT UP BETWEEN THE DIFFERENT COMPANIES. IT TOOK A LONG TIME, BUT I WAS FINALLY ABLE TO CATCH UP ON MY BILLS. THEN I WAS LAID OFF FROM WORK. UNEMPLOYMENT INSURANCE WAS NOT ENOUGH TO PAY BOTH MY RENT AND CREDIT BILLS, SO I HAD TO BECOME LATE AGAIN ON MY CREDIT. ONCE THE LAYOFF WAS OVER, I AGAIN WAS ABLE TO GATHER MY BILLS, CALCULATE WHAT I OWED TO EACH COMPANY, AND STARTED THE SLOW PROCESS OF CATCHING UP ON MY CREDIT BILLS. AFTER SEVERAL MONTHS, I WAS CAUGHT UP. DUE TO A RELAPSE OF THE ACCIDENT I HAD, I WENT TO THE HOSPITAL, AND WAS NOT ABLE TO WORK FOR 6 MONTHS. ONCE I GOT OUT OF THE HOSPITAL, I THEN CAUGHT UP MY BILLS AFTER ABOUT A THREE MONTH PERIOD.
